description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within Kent Community Health NHS Foundation Trust, to join our clinical team of LAC nurses working with children and young people in care.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We provide our nursing service from various bases across Kent. This is a diverse health role working closely with children and young people, their carers and multi-agency partners. You will also be expected to work at the interface between health, local authorities and partner agencies to drive forward the national and local agenda for the health of looked after children.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are a registered nurse with SCPHN/community paediatric/sexual health/mental health experience, we would like to hear from you. Experience of working with children and young people with complex health and social needs, including emotional health difficulties and, or learning difficulties would be advantageous. You should be able to work innovatively and involve young people in decisions about their care and gain young people&#39;s views about their services they receive in order to continually improve service delivery.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The essential qualities we are looking for in our applicants are:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Flexible and dynamic working&lt;br /&gt;Excellent problem-solving abilities&lt;br /&gt;Partnership working and excellent communication skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Car owner/driver essential, subject to the provisions of the Equality Act (2010)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Interviews to be held on 16th November 2020 via Microsoft Teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This vacancy will be located at The Whitstable Health Centre and the focus of your work will be primarily in the East/South Kent area, however at times you may be required to cover the West Kent area according to service need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tanya Spain - Named Nurse for Looked After Children KCHFT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: tanya.spain@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone: 0782454088&lt;/p&gt;
